Definition: an artistic movement in the United States that was derived from the Hudson River school
Example: active from 1850 to 1870; painted realistic landscapes in a style that pictured atmospheric light and the use of aerial perspective
Synonyms: artistic_movement, an, artistic, movement, in, the, United, States, that, was, derived, from, Hudson, River, school, active, to, painted, realistic, landscapes, a, style, pictured, atmospheric, light, and, use, of, aerial, perspective
Category: noun.group
